		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nope, you have to do a garbage read of $2007 any time you change the VRAM address (except by the auto-inc).  The garbage read is actually reading what was previously in the buffer, and filling it with the byte at the specified VRAM address for the next read.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


