	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Using the term "garbage read" is misleading since it implies that the buffer is somehow filled regularly with garbage, which is not the case. $2007 reads are buffered, which is best thought of as delaying things rather than returning garbage (except when reading palette RAM where there is no "delay", though the buffer is still invisibly refilled as if there were no palette RAM).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


